Avoid transforming family heirlooms into 3-D pieces. This will damage the integrity of the item and probably motivate your grandmother to write you out of her will. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4a/Create-3D-Jars-and-Vases-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Create-3D-Jars-and-Vases-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4a/Create-3D-Jars-and-Vases-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Create-3D-Jars-and-Vases-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
